90
00:06:58,120 --> 00:07:00,480
 The water that I shall give him will become in him

91
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:04,040
 a spring of water welling up to eternal life.

92
00:07:04,040 --> 00:07:07,440
 The woman said to him, sir, give me this water

93
00:07:07,440 --> 00:07:10,760
 that I may not thirst, nor come here to draw.

94
00:07:10,760 --> 00:07:23,900
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

95
00:07:23,900 --> 00:07:26,200
 Here, what is the difference between the living water

96
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:29,200
 that Jesus speaks of and the water in the well?

97
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:31,440
 The passage mentions that the woman's response raises

98
00:07:31,440 --> 00:07:34,080
 questions about racial identity.

99
00:07:34,080 --> 00:07:36,240
 And what is the relationship between the Jew

100
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:38,440
 and the Samaritan?

101
00:07:38,440 --> 00:08:08,320
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

102
00:08:08,320 --> 00:08:18,920
 And Jesus said to her, go, call your husband, and come here.

103
