 The woman answered him, I have no husband.

104
00:08:22,080 --> 00:08:24,560
 Jesus said to her, you are right in saying,

105
00:08:24,560 --> 00:08:28,040
 I have no husband, for you have had five husbands,

106
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:31,640
 and he whom you now have is not your husband.

107
00:08:31,640 --> 00:08:33,640
 This you say truly.

108
00:08:33,640 --> 00:08:35,800
 The woman said to him, sir, I perceive

109
00:08:35,800 --> 00:08:38,560
 that you are a prophet, a father's worship

110
00:08:38,560 --> 00:08:41,200
 on this mountain, and you say that in Jerusalem

111
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:44,800
 is the place where men ought to worship.

112
00:08:44,800 --> 00:09:06,280
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

113
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:22,640
 Jesus said to her, woman, believe me,

114
00:09:22,640 --> 00:09:25,160
 the hour is coming when neither on this mountain

115
00:09:25,160 --> 00:09:28,600
 nor in Jerusalem will you worship the Father.

116
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:30,320
 You worship what you do not know.

117
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:34,360
 We worship what we know, for salvation is from the Jews.

118
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:36,760
 But the hour is coming, and now is,

119
00:09:36,760 --> 00:09:39,240
 when the true worshipers will worship the Father

120
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:41,040
 in spirit and truth.

121
00:09:41,040 --> 00:09:43,960
 For such, the Father seeks to worship him.

122
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:46,160
 God is spirit, and those who worship him

123
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:48,760
 must worship in spirit and truth.

124
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:51,960
 The woman said to him, I know that Messiah is coming,

125
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:53,400
 he who is called Christ.

126
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:56,800
 And when he comes, he will show us all things.

127
00:09:56,800 --> 00:10:02,440
 Jesus said to her, I who speak to you am he.

128
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:04,960
 I am he, yeah.

129
00:10:04,960 --> 00:10:15,760
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

130
00:10:15,760 --> 00:10:17,760
 So this is a long dialogue describing how

131
00:10:17,760 --> 00:10:20,000
 the woman interact with Jesus.

132
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:22,080
 But after that, she was changed.

133
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:25,560
 So what is the change that happened in her?

134
00:10:25,560 --> 00:10:35,200
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

135
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:38,680
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

136
00:10:38,680 --> 00:10:42,080
 First, why did Jesus have to pass through Samaria?

137
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:45,480
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

138
00:10:45,480 --> 00:10:47,680
 Second, what is the difference between the living water

139
00:10:47,680 --> 00:10:50,000
 that Jesus spoke about and the water in the well?

140
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:55,640
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

141
00:10:55,640 --> 00:10:58,040
 And third, what obvious change do we see in the woman

142
00:10:58,040 --> 00:11:01,080
 after she heard Jesus' word?

143
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:03,960
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

144
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:06,520
 So let's answer the first question.

145
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:09,520
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

146
00:11:09,520 --> 00:11:12,400
 Why did Jesus have to pass through Samaria?

147
00:11:12,400 --> 00:11:19,360
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

148
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:22,760
 Our passage says that Jesus left Judea for Galilee,

149
00:11:22,760 --> 00:11:25,400
 and he had to pass through Samaria.

150
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:34,040
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

151
00:11:34,040 --> 00:11:36,000
 Here he came to a city called Sychar,

152
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:37,760
 near the piece of land that Jacob

153
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:39,720
 had given to his son Joseph.

154
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:42,160
 And it mentions that Jacob's well was there.

155
00:11:42,160 --> 00:11:51,840
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

156
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:54,120
 And according to the customs of the Jews at that time,

157
00:11:54,120 --> 00:11:56,000
 they often preferred to take a detour

158
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:58,200
 rather than passing through Samaria,

159
00:11:58,200 --> 00:12:00,880
 because there was a deep religious and ethnic hatred

160
00:12:00,880 --> 00:12:02,360
 between the two groups.

161
00:12:02,360 --> 00:12:15,440
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

162
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:18,800
 But John tells that Jesus had to pass through Samaria.

163
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:22,120
 This "had to" is not a geographical necessity,

164
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:25,200
 but a necessity in the plan of salvation.

165
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:27,640
 Jesus was there to find someone and through her

166
00:12:27,640 --> 00:12:29,000
 to find the lost.

167
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:36,560
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

168
00:12:36,560 --> 00:12:38,720
 If you've seen this slide, it's made with AI,

169
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:42,600
 and it's a map of following Jesus' route.

170
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:46,360
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

171
00:12:46,360 --> 00:12:49,360
 And there are three main areas in these pictures,

172
00:12:49,360 --> 00:12:51,280
 from bottom to top.

173
00:12:51,280 --> 00:12:56,800
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

174
00:12:56,800 --> 00:12:59,880
 To the south lies Judea, which is

175
00:12:59,880 --> 00:13:01,640
 where Jerusalem and Bethlehem is.

176
00:13:01,640 --> 00:13:04,080
 And that is the orange section.

177
00:13:04,080 --> 00:13:07,400
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

178
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:12,440
 In the middle is Samaria, which is the yellow section.

179
00:13:12,440 --> 00:13:14,600
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

180
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:16,560
 And to the north lies Galilee, which

181
00:13:16,560 --> 00:13:18,880
 is the one section in green.

182
00:13:18,880 --> 00:13:22,040
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

183
00:13:22,040 --> 00:13:24,640
 Then there's two lines, the red lines.

184
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:44,280
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

185
00:13:44,280 --> 00:13:46,080
 One of the route is the one that Jesus took,

186
00:13:46,080 --> 00:13:49,800
 going straight north from Judea along the mountains

187
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:52,280
 through Samaria to Galilee.

188
00:13:52,280 --> 00:13:55,160
 This is the straight and the shortest route, like the line

189
00:13:55,160 --> 00:13:58,560
 on the map from Jerusalem passing through Samaria.

190
00:13:58,560 --> 00:14:26,820
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

191
00:14:26,820 --> 00:14:31,040
 Another route frequently used by the Jews was to bypass Samaria.

192
00:14:31,040 --> 00:14:33,840
 They would first travel east to the Jordan River,

193
00:14:33,840 --> 00:14:36,520
 and then through Jericho, cross the river,

194
00:14:36,520 --> 00:14:39,360
 and then travel north along the east bank.

195
00:14:39,360 --> 00:14:41,680
 And once they get north, they would cross the river again

196
00:14:41,680 --> 00:14:43,280
 to return to Galilee.

197
00:14:43,280 --> 00:14:46,400
 And this is the so-called East Jordan-Periyah route,

198
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:48,120
 a detour route that is deliberately

199
00:14:48,120 --> 00:14:50,520
 used to avoid Samaria.

200
00:14:50,520 --> 00:15:03,080
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

201
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:04,880
 This is because the Jews have always

202
00:15:04,880 --> 00:15:08,040
 believed that the Samaritans, they were not pure Jews.

203
00:15:08,040 --> 00:15:10,960
 They were once a tribe of the northern kingdom of Israel,

204
00:15:10,960 --> 00:15:13,160
 but they intermarried with the outsider.

205
00:15:13,160 --> 00:15:15,600
 And thus, they defiled the Jewish bloodline.

206
00:15:15,600 --> 00:15:17,800
 And they were considered as mixed race.

207
00:15:17,800 --> 00:15:22,440
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

208
00:15:22,440 --> 00:15:23,960
 Moreover, the Samaritans had also

209
00:15:23,960 --> 00:15:27,800
 joined forces with outsiders to kill the Jews of the south.

210
00:15:27,800 --> 00:15:39,480
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

211
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:41,120
 And this turned the two nations who

212
00:15:41,120 --> 00:15:43,000
 share the same origin and ethnicity

213
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:45,680
 into bitter enemies, with no contact

214
00:15:45,680 --> 00:15:47,440
 and mutual hostilities.

215
00:15:47,440 --> 00:15:49,440
 And this is somewhat similar to the current relationship

216
00:15:49,440 --> 00:15:51,040
 between the North Korean government

217
00:15:51,040 --> 00:15:52,520
 and the South Korean government.

218
00:15:52,520 --> 00:16:03,520
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

219
00:16:03,520 --> 00:16:05,440
 If you look at the map, going through Samaria

220
00:16:05,440 --> 00:16:08,280
 is a reasonable and common route.

221
00:16:08,280 --> 00:16:10,040
 But it is not the only route.

222
00:16:10,040 --> 00:16:12,520
 Jesus used the alternative routes--

223
00:16:12,520 --> 00:16:14,360
 the Jews would use the alternative routes

224
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:16,040
 to avoid Samaria.

225
00:16:16,040 --> 00:16:34,240
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

226
00:16:34,240 --> 00:16:37,040
 When Jesus says in chapter 4 that he

227
00:16:37,040 --> 00:16:38,680
 had to pass through Samaria, the point

228
00:16:38,680 --> 00:16:42,800
 is not that he was forced to take a detour by the terrain,

229
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:45,080
 but that according to the Father's will,

230
00:16:45,080 --> 00:16:49,960
 he deliberately chose this route that most people would avoid,

231
00:16:49,960 --> 00:16:52,000
 so that he could meet the Samaritan woman there

232
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:54,360
 and bring salvation to the entire city.

233
00:16:54,360 --> 00:17:01,680
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

234
00:17:01,680 --> 00:17:04,520
 So Jesus deliberately passes through this place,

235
00:17:04,520 --> 00:17:06,320
 breaking down the longstanding divide

236
00:17:06,320 --> 00:17:09,640
 and mutual hatred between the Jews and the Samaritans.

237
00:17:09,640 --> 00:17:20,720
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

238
00:17:20,720 --> 00:17:23,760
 Jesus did this to reaffirm that salvation was not only

239
00:17:23,760 --> 00:17:26,800
 for the Jews, but also for some peoples who were looked down

240
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:29,720
 upon and considered unworthy of salvation,

241
00:17:29,720 --> 00:17:32,560
 such as the mixed-race Samaritans.

242
00:17:32,560 --> 00:17:41,880
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

243
00:17:41,880 --> 00:17:45,120
 This simple sentence crosses several boundaries.

244
00:17:45,120 --> 00:17:51,160
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

245
00:17:51,160 --> 00:17:56,000
 It was very unusual for a man to speak to a woman at that time.

246
00:17:56,000 --> 00:18:03,400
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

247
00:18:03,400 --> 00:18:06,040
 And the fact that the Jews is the one who took the initiative

248
00:18:06,040 --> 00:18:10,200
 to ask the Samaritan for water is even more unconventional.

249
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:12,840
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

250
00:18:12,840 --> 00:18:16,320
 And yet Jesus set an example for us by doing this.

251
00:18:16,320 --> 00:18:18,280
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

252
00:18:18,280 --> 00:18:20,880
 So are you willing to pass through your Samaria?

253
00:18:20,880 --> 00:18:26,800
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH] In our lives, there might be places

254
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:29,920
 or people that we don't want to pass through.

255
00:18:29,920 --> 00:18:35,120
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

256
00:18:35,120 --> 00:18:38,760
 Maybe it's the colleague who everyone dislikes and always

257
00:18:38,760 --> 00:18:40,000
 being joked about.

258
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:46,400
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

259
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:48,720
 Or the relatives who always speak hurtfully

260
00:18:48,720 --> 00:18:50,320
 at family gatherings.

261
00:18:50,320 --> 00:18:55,640
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

262
00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:57,080
 Or the neighbor in your community

263
00:18:57,080 --> 00:19:00,840
 who speaks with an accent and has a very different culture.

264
00:19:00,840 --> 00:19:08,880
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

265
00:19:08,880 --> 00:19:11,240
 One time, a brother shared that there was a new immigrant

266
00:19:11,240 --> 00:19:13,480
 in his company, and his coworkers all say,

267
00:19:13,480 --> 00:19:14,960
 don't pay attention to him.

268
00:19:14,960 --> 00:19:17,880
 His English is not good, and he doesn't understand the culture.

269
00:19:17,880 --> 00:19:32,760
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

270
00:19:32,760 --> 00:19:35,080
 One day, while he was reading John chapter 4,

271
00:19:35,080 --> 00:19:38,800
 he was deeply moved when he read about this Jesus sitting

272
00:19:38,800 --> 00:19:41,320
 by the well and saying to the Samaritan woman,

273
00:19:41,320 --> 00:19:42,400
 give me a drink.

274
00:19:42,400 --> 00:19:44,840
 So he decided to invite his colleague to lunch

275
00:19:44,840 --> 00:19:47,960
 so that he could hear him talk about his hometown and his family.

276
00:19:47,960 --> 00:20:01,680
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

277
00:20:01,680 --> 00:20:03,360
 After a few meals together, the colleague

278
00:20:03,360 --> 00:20:05,480
 said, you are the first person who really

279
00:20:05,480 --> 00:20:06,960
 wants to understand me.

280
00:20:06,960 --> 00:20:09,640
 And from then on, this brother became his first impression

281
00:20:09,640 --> 00:20:12,000
 of Christian.

282
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:22,100
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

283
00:20:22,100 --> 00:20:25,040
 So Brian's sister, this is the kind of God that Jesus is.

284
00:20:25,040 --> 00:20:28,160
 He doesn't just wait for people to come to him in the temple,

285
00:20:28,160 --> 00:20:31,960
 but he goes to the well and to the despised place.

286
00:20:31,960 --> 00:20:44,600
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

287
00:20:44,600 --> 00:20:49,160
 Today, he's also calling us, who is the Samaritan besides us?

288
00:20:49,160 --> 00:20:50,960
 And are you willing to deliberately make

289
00:20:50,960 --> 00:20:54,400
 a trip for the Lord, seemingly by possible,

290
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:59,560
 but actually prepared by God, encountered by the well?

291
00:20:59,560 --> 00:21:10,200
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

292
00:21:10,200 --> 00:21:13,080
 Jesus not only spoke to her across the barrier,

293
00:21:13,080 --> 00:21:16,680
 but he was also not content with just giving her water,

294
00:21:16,680 --> 00:21:18,840
 as if to quench her thirst temporarily.

295
00:21:18,840 --> 00:21:21,560
 And so the next scene will show the transformation

296
00:21:21,560 --> 00:21:23,720
 from well water to living water.

297
00:21:23,720 --> 00:21:25,680
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

298
00:21:25,680 --> 00:21:27,120
 To answer the second question.

299
00:21:27,120 --> 00:21:30,560
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

300
00:21:30,560 --> 00:21:32,720
 What is the difference between the living water

301
00:21:32,720 --> 00:21:35,360
 that Jesus spoke about and the water in the well?

302
00:21:35,360 --> 00:21:40,360
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

303
00:21:40,360 --> 00:21:41,960
 The well water and living water here

304
00:21:41,960 --> 00:21:46,000
 are the tools that Jesus used to touch our deepest desire.

305
00:21:46,000 --> 00:22:00,960
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

306
00:22:00,960 --> 00:22:03,240
 When the woman was surprised that Jesus would ask her

307
00:22:03,240 --> 00:22:05,600
 for water, Jesus turned the conversation

308
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:07,320
 into something deeper.

309
00:22:07,320 --> 00:22:10,680
 If you knew the gift of God and who it is that says to you,

310
00:22:10,680 --> 00:22:13,040
 give me a drink, you would have asked him,

311
00:22:13,040 --> 00:22:15,120
 and he would have given you living water.

312
00:22:15,120 --> 00:22:23,600
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

313
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:25,840
 At first, she only thought of the actual well water.

314
00:22:25,840 --> 00:22:28,800
 So she said, sir, you don't have tools to draw water,

315
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:30,320
 and the well is deep.

316
00:22:30,320 --> 00:22:32,440
 Where will you get this fresh water?

317
00:22:32,440 --> 00:22:43,360
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

318
00:22:43,360 --> 00:22:45,520
 But Jesus said, anyone who drinks this water

319
00:22:45,520 --> 00:22:46,760
 will thirst again.

320
00:22:46,760 --> 00:22:50,040
 But whoever drinks the water I give them will never thirst.

321
00:22:50,040 --> 00:22:52,000
 And the water I give them will become in them

322
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:55,320
 a spring of water welling up to eternal life.

323
00:22:55,320 --> 00:23:04,280
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

324
00:23:04,280 --> 00:23:07,760
 So the thirst here is no longer just a physical thirst,

325
00:23:07,760 --> 00:23:10,960
 but a deep spiritual emptiness and the desperate desires

326
00:23:10,960 --> 00:23:12,240
 of the soul.

327
00:23:12,240 --> 00:23:31,120
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

328
00:23:31,120 --> 00:23:33,640
 Jesus mentioned that she had five husbands

329
00:23:33,640 --> 00:23:36,800
 and that the one she had now was not her husband.

330
00:23:36,800 --> 00:23:39,960
 This was not to humiliate her, but to gently reveal

331
00:23:39,960 --> 00:23:42,960
 the deep longing she had been trying to feel with all

332
00:23:42,960 --> 00:23:45,360
 these relationships and marriage--

333
00:23:45,360 --> 00:23:48,160
 to be loved, accepted, and affirmed.

334
00:23:48,160 --> 00:23:58,880
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

335
00:23:58,880 --> 00:24:01,640
 Many scholars have pointed out that her multiple marriages

336
00:24:01,640 --> 00:24:05,520
 were likely the results of being divorced or widowed repeatedly.

337
00:24:05,520 --> 00:24:08,560
 And these were the signs of being hurt.

338
00:24:08,560 --> 00:24:12,840
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

339
00:24:12,840 --> 00:24:14,000
 Today we do the same thing.

340
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:16,880
 We constantly search for various kinds of water.

341
00:24:16,880 --> 00:24:21,320
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

342
00:24:21,320 --> 00:24:23,920
 Some people quench their thirst with achievements--

343
00:24:23,920 --> 00:24:26,680
 promotions, raises, and titles.

344
00:24:26,680 --> 00:24:31,760
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

345
00:24:31,760 --> 00:24:34,560
 But some people quench their thirst with emotions--

346
00:24:34,560 --> 00:24:37,760
 dating, changing partners, hoping that this time they

347
00:24:37,760 --> 00:24:39,560
 will truly be loved.

348
00:24:39,560 --> 00:24:48,200
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

349
00:24:48,200 --> 00:24:51,000
 And some people quench their thirst with entertainment--

350
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:53,560
 binge-watching TV series, playing games,

351
00:24:53,560 --> 00:24:55,960
 and social medias, just to prevent themselves

352
00:24:55,960 --> 00:24:59,880
 from having the time to sit with their inner thoughts.

353
00:24:59,880 --> 00:25:12,360
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

354
00:25:12,360 --> 00:25:15,400
 This is similar to a phone constantly using power.

355
00:25:15,400 --> 00:25:17,280
 The screen is on, programs are running,

356
00:25:17,280 --> 00:25:19,000
 and the videos are being watched.

357
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:21,360
 And this, on the surface, seems very likely.

358
00:25:21,360 --> 00:25:25,280
 But if the charging cable is not plugged into the actual power,

359
00:25:25,280 --> 00:25:28,440
 it will not charge, no matter how long you plug it in.

360
00:25:28,440 --> 00:25:45,040
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

361
00:25:45,040 --> 00:25:46,960
 Maybe you can feel your schedule every day,

362
00:25:46,960 --> 00:25:48,680
 pack your shopping cart to the brim,

363
00:25:48,680 --> 00:25:52,000
 and the friend list on your social media is filled.

364
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:56,080
 But the true yearning in your heart of, do I have any value?

365
00:25:56,080 --> 00:26:00,240
 Or am I truly known and truly loved, remains unsolved.

366
00:26:00,240 --> 00:26:04,000
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

367
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:06,440
 Jesus said to the woman, whoever drinks this water

368
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:08,000
 will be thirsty again.

369
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:16,280
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

370
00:26:16,280 --> 00:26:20,040
 Today, he is also saying to us, children, what you really need

371
00:26:20,040 --> 00:26:23,640
 is not to change the well, but to change the water,

372
00:26:23,640 --> 00:26:28,000
 not to change the object, but to change the source.

373
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:47,400
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

374
00:26:47,400 --> 00:26:48,880
 He will give us the Holy Spirit so

375
00:26:48,880 --> 00:26:51,880
 that we may worship the Father in spirit and truth,

376
00:26:51,880 --> 00:26:53,600
 so that our lives are not supported

377
00:26:53,600 --> 00:26:57,720
 by actual circumstances, but have a living spring within us,

378
00:26:57,720 --> 00:27:00,960
 so that we can still receive comfort and strength from God

379
00:27:00,960 --> 00:27:04,320
 when we encounter pressure, loneliness, and loss.

380
00:27:04,320 --> 00:27:16,400
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

381
00:27:16,400 --> 00:27:18,040
 Perhaps you're sitting in a room today,

382
00:27:18,040 --> 00:27:20,960
 and everything seems fine from the outside.

383
00:27:20,960 --> 00:27:24,320
 A complete family, a stable job, and a busy ministry.

384
00:27:24,320 --> 00:27:27,960
 But only you who can know the real thirst

385
00:27:27,960 --> 00:27:29,760
 that is in your heart.

386
00:27:29,760 --> 00:27:39,400
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

387
00:27:39,400 --> 00:27:42,960
 And today, the Lord is saying to you, bring your water jug

388
00:27:42,960 --> 00:27:45,840
 and give up everything you use to quench your thirst,

389
00:27:45,840 --> 00:27:47,760
 and let me be your living water.

390
00:27:50,680 --> 00:28:02,200
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

391
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:04,440
 In the moment the woman tasted the living water,

392
00:28:04,440 --> 00:28:06,480
 her new life showed a sign.

393
00:28:06,480 --> 00:28:10,000
 She put down the water jug and ran back to the city.

394
00:28:10,000 --> 00:28:11,840
 This leads us to the third scene,

395
00:28:11,840 --> 00:28:13,880
 the testimony of putting down the water jug.

396
00:28:13,880 --> 00:28:15,880
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

397
00:28:15,880 --> 00:28:17,880
 And this is also answering our third question.

398
00:28:17,880 --> 00:28:22,520
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

399
00:28:22,520 --> 00:28:24,600
 What obvious change occurred in the woman

400
00:28:24,600 --> 00:28:26,640
 after she heard Jesus' word?

401
00:28:26,640 --> 00:28:36,360
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

402
00:28:36,360 --> 00:28:38,720
 Scripture says that then the woman left the water jug

403
00:28:38,720 --> 00:28:41,680
 behind and went into the city, saying to the crowd,

404
00:28:41,680 --> 00:28:45,360
 come and see a man who has told me everything I've ever done.

405
00:28:45,360 --> 00:28:48,320
 Could this be the Messiah?

406
00:28:48,320 --> 00:29:06,040
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

407
00:29:06,040 --> 00:29:08,080
 So many Samaritans believe in Jesus

408
00:29:08,080 --> 00:29:09,880
 because of what the woman said.

409
00:29:09,880 --> 00:29:13,680
 And later, because they heard him speak, many more believed.

410
00:29:13,680 --> 00:29:16,560
 And they're saying, now we believe no more

411
00:29:16,560 --> 00:29:18,600
 because of what you say, but because we

412
00:29:18,600 --> 00:29:22,400
 have heard it ourselves and know that he is indeed the Savior.

413
00:29:22,400 --> 00:29:24,240
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

414
00:29:24,240 --> 00:29:25,840
 Note the following.

415
00:29:25,840 --> 00:29:35,120
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

416
00:29:35,120 --> 00:29:38,040
 This Samaritan woman hasn't gone through any discipleship

417
00:29:38,040 --> 00:29:40,600
 courses or received any preaching training.

418
00:29:40,600 --> 00:29:45,640
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

419
00:29:45,640 --> 00:29:47,800
 Her path is still messy, and many of her wounds

420
00:29:47,800 --> 00:29:50,160
 still remains, but she has met the Lord.

421
00:29:50,160 --> 00:29:58,120
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

422
00:29:58,120 --> 00:30:01,440
 And her sermons were simple, not a systematic theology,

423
00:30:01,440 --> 00:30:03,520
 but just come and see.

424
00:30:03,520 --> 00:30:05,720
 Come and see the Lord who sees me entirely

425
00:30:05,720 --> 00:30:07,760
 but has not abandoned me.

426
00:30:07,760 --> 00:30:13,600
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

427
00:30:13,600 --> 00:30:15,720
 And God used this broken woman to become

428
00:30:15,720 --> 00:30:17,800
 the first missionaries to the city,

429
00:30:17,800 --> 00:30:20,040
 preparing the way for Jesus.

430
00:30:20,040 --> 00:30:25,960
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

431
00:30:25,960 --> 00:30:28,440
 One of the sister had recently become a believer,

432
00:30:28,440 --> 00:30:31,680
 and she didn't understand the Bible very well yet.

433
00:30:31,680 --> 00:30:35,600
 And she also hadn't completely changed many of her bad temper.

434
00:30:35,600 --> 00:30:39,880
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

435
00:30:39,880 --> 00:30:43,000
 But when she returned to her company, people asked her,

436
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:44,840
 oh, you seem a little bit different today.

437
00:30:44,840 --> 00:30:51,720
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

438
00:30:51,720 --> 00:30:53,400
 So she answered awkwardly, I recently

439
00:30:53,400 --> 00:30:55,360
 went to church and met Jesus.

440
00:30:55,360 --> 00:30:57,160
 I don't know how to explain it, but it just

441
00:30:57,160 --> 00:30:58,640
 makes me feel more at peace.

442
00:30:58,640 --> 00:31:12,520
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

443
00:31:12,520 --> 00:31:14,040
 Because of that, her co-worker, who

444
00:31:14,040 --> 00:31:16,400
 noticed that she was less likely to lose control

445
00:31:16,400 --> 00:31:20,120
 under pressure and more gentle when she was being criticized,

446
00:31:20,120 --> 00:31:22,280
 they asked her, next time when you go to church,

447
00:31:22,280 --> 00:31:23,920
 can I go with you?

448
00:31:23,920 --> 00:31:29,600
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

449
00:31:29,600 --> 00:31:32,520
 She was not a perfect Christian, but she

450
00:31:32,520 --> 00:31:35,120
 was a true witness like the Samaritan woman.

451
00:31:35,120 --> 00:31:37,520
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

452
00:31:37,520 --> 00:31:39,680
 So today, God is also asking us these questions.

453
00:31:39,680 --> 00:31:45,400
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

454
00:31:45,400 --> 00:31:47,080
 Would you be willing to be like her,

455
00:31:47,080 --> 00:31:49,320
 to put down your water jug and stop

456
00:31:49,320 --> 00:31:51,320
 spending your whole life just to fetch water

457
00:31:51,320 --> 00:31:52,320
 for your own thirst?

458
00:31:52,320 --> 00:32:01,440
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

459
00:32:01,440 --> 00:32:04,240
 Would you be willing to go back to your own city, your home,

460
00:32:04,240 --> 00:32:06,480
 your workplace, your social circle,

461
00:32:06,480 --> 00:32:09,800
 and share honestly on how God has worked in you just

462
00:32:09,800 --> 00:32:11,040
 like she did?

463
00:32:11,040 --> 00:32:22,360
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

464
00:32:22,360 --> 00:32:24,960
 You don't need to be able to explain all the theology.

465
00:32:24,960 --> 00:32:26,360
 All you need is just a willingness

466
00:32:26,360 --> 00:32:28,200
 to say, come and see.

467
00:32:28,200 --> 00:32:29,960
 And the Lord can use your few words

468
00:32:29,960 --> 00:32:33,840
 to awaken the thirst in one's heart and bring them to Jesus.

469
00:32:33,840 --> 00:32:36,400
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

470
00:32:36,400 --> 00:32:39,240
 So the scripture answered us three questions.

471
00:32:39,240 --> 00:32:45,000
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

472
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:47,120
 Before we end, I would like to invite everyone

473
00:32:47,120 --> 00:32:50,440
 to response with these three questions before the Lord.

474
00:32:50,440 --> 00:32:52,560
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

475
00:32:52,560 --> 00:32:55,640
 First, where is your Samaria?

476
00:32:55,640 --> 00:33:09,640
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

477
00:33:09,640 --> 00:33:13,040
 Today, Jesus might be waiting for you by your well.

478
00:33:13,040 --> 00:33:16,560
 Perhaps it is your daily commute in front of your work seat

479
00:33:16,560 --> 00:33:19,080
 or the sofa in your living room.

480
00:33:19,080 --> 00:33:25,960
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

481
00:33:25,960 --> 00:33:28,560
 Would you be willing to stop at the most ordinary places

482
00:33:28,560 --> 00:33:31,120
 in your daily life and listen to him?

483
00:33:31,120 --> 00:33:33,440
 Take a step forward and reach out to the people

484
00:33:33,440 --> 00:33:35,800
 that you wouldn't normally encounter.

485
00:33:35,800 --> 00:33:38,120
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

486
00:33:38,120 --> 00:33:40,680
 Second, what is your deepest desire?

487
00:33:40,680 --> 00:33:45,440
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

488
00:33:45,440 --> 00:33:48,840
 Perhaps it is a desire for relationships or achievements

489
00:33:48,840 --> 00:33:55,280
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

490
00:33:55,280 --> 00:33:57,240
 Perhaps you can't even explain it yourself.

491
00:33:57,240 --> 00:33:59,480
 You just know that you're tired and empty.

492
00:33:59,480 --> 00:34:02,360
 And all you know is that you need to earn more and more.

493
00:34:02,360 --> 00:34:11,160
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

494
00:34:11,160 --> 00:34:14,120
 So today, are you willing to bring all of this before the Lord

495
00:34:14,120 --> 00:34:17,960
 and say to him, Lord, I no longer want the well water.

496
00:34:17,960 --> 00:34:21,840
 I want the living water that only you can give.

497
00:34:21,840 --> 00:34:23,360
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

498
00:34:23,360 --> 00:34:25,640
 Third, who is your city?

499
00:34:25,640 --> 00:34:35,120
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

500
00:34:35,120 --> 00:34:37,640
 Who are some of the people in your life that God has placed?

501
00:34:37,640 --> 00:34:40,880
 Maybe your family, your coworkers, your classmates

502
00:34:40,880 --> 00:34:43,600
 that Jesus wants to invite them through you.

503
00:34:43,600 --> 00:34:45,200
 Come and see.

504
00:34:45,200 --> 00:34:56,160
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

505
00:34:56,160 --> 00:34:58,080
 Are you willing to pray for them this week,

506
00:34:58,080 --> 00:34:59,840
 asking God to give you the opportunity

507
00:34:59,840 --> 00:35:03,280
 to take that extra step, to say that extra words,

508
00:35:03,280 --> 00:35:07,240
 or to show an extra care for one of them this week?

509
00:35:07,240 --> 00:35:08,520
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

510
00:35:08,520 --> 00:35:11,800
 Let us pray together.

511
00:35:11,800 --> 00:35:28,280
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

512
00:35:28,280 --> 00:35:30,520
 Lord Jesus, we confess that we often

513
00:35:30,520 --> 00:35:34,440
 try to quench the thirst in our heart with a lot of well water.

514
00:35:34,440 --> 00:35:35,960
 But thank you for reminding us today

515
00:35:35,960 --> 00:35:39,280
 that you are the true living water, the Messiah who

516
00:35:39,280 --> 00:35:44,440
 transcends all barriers, and yet you wait for us by the well.

517
00:35:44,440 --> 00:36:02,640
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

518
00:36:02,640 --> 00:36:04,840
 Lord, would you heal our past brokenness

519
00:36:04,840 --> 00:36:07,680
 and be the spring of water within us.

520
00:36:07,680 --> 00:36:09,360
 Heal us, like the Samaritan woman,

521
00:36:09,360 --> 00:36:12,720
 to be a true witness in our home, in our workplace,

522
00:36:12,720 --> 00:36:15,120
 and in our circle of friends.

523
00:36:15,120 --> 00:36:18,640
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

524
00:36:18,640 --> 00:36:21,840
 Bring people to you in the name of Jesus.

525
00:36:21,840 --> 00:36:22,360
 Amen.

526
00:36:22,360 --> 00:36:23,920
 Amen.

527
00:36:23,920 --> 00:36:26,360
 [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

